Ethnic violence resulted in 148 deaths and 885 injuries in Kirghizia, a republic in Central  Asia.
The violence occurred in western Kirghizia near the border where Kirghiz and  Uzbeks were fighting over the allocation of a piece of land.
The Soviet Interior Ministry said that in the past two years of civil strife, primarily ethnic  clashes, 24,000 had been killed and 16 ministry soldiers killed.
Ministry troops had been  used in 13 regions of the Soviet Union because of ethnic disputes.
Beside the unrest in  Kirghizia and Uzbekistan, serious fighting has taken place in Georgia, Armenia,  Azerbaijan and Kazakhstan. 
